{
  "text": "RNA was isolated from livers of 2-d-old chicks by the method of Chirgwin et al. [CITATION_1] . Poly (A+)-enriched RNA was isolated by one cycle of oligothymidylic acid-cellulose (Boehringer Mannheim Diagnostics, Inc.) chromatography according to the method of Aviv and Leder [CITATION_2] . Poly (A+)-enriched RNA was reverse transcribed to cDNA using the Invitrogen (San Diego, CA) Reverse Transcription kit following the manufacturer's instructions.",
  "citation_candidates": [
